Dear Hiring Team,

It is with great pleasure that I submit my candidacy for the *Software Engineer* role with *Spring Health*. I bring over three years of professional experience in full-stack and front-end web development, along with a strong academic foundation as a Master of Science in Computer Science graduate from Pace University, NY.

Through my experience across two engineering roles, I have built and delivered production-grade full-stack systems that directly reflect the technical depth the Top of Funnel team demands. As a Software Engineer at Sperse, I designed and delivered full-stack and front-end features using TypeScript-typed API contracts — requiring rigorous input validation, safe execution, and reliable user-facing behavior across 1,000+ platform endpoints. To keep these systems production-ready, I built a full observability layer using Datadog-compatible tracing via LangSmith and Langfuse, covering structured logs, Sentry-style error capture, and evaluation hooks — reducing end-to-end latency by 60% and costs by 50% through targeted concurrency optimizations. I also shipped 0-1 product features in cross-functional Agile sprints, contributed to code reviews, documentation, and test coverage standards, and collaborated across distributed teams — all of which map directly to what success looks like in this role. Prior to Sperse, as a Software Engineer at Qualitest, I contributed to an Identity & Access Management platform covering top of funnel authentication, registration, and onboarding flows built with React, Spring Boot, and AWS, supporting thousands of users across 30+ applications — directly mirroring the Member Growth team's ownership of the critical first steps in a member's journey. I also designed a GraphQL-ready cloud-agnostic Storage Service using Python, PostgreSQL, and Redis, and developed AWS Step Functions workflows to handle long-running data import jobs — both requiring the systems-level thinking and operational stability focus this role demands.

My academic research experience has given me a rigorous foundation in model development and technical communication — skills that translate directly into the engineering discipline and collaborative culture Spring Health values. As an AI Researcher at the Pace Artificial Intelligence Lab, I managed the full model development lifecycle from training to inference optimization and deployment, and led workshops on GPU programming and AI Agents for 50+ students — designing and delivering those sessions required me to break down complex technical concepts clearly and accessibly, directly mirroring the knowledge-sharing and cross-functional collaboration central to this team.

I have always been passionate about making technology accessible and inclusive, and Spring Health's mission to eliminate every barrier to mental health — delivering the right care at the right time through Precision Mental Healthcare tailored to each individual — is exactly the kind of goal I want to build toward. The Top of Funnel team's work sits at the intersection of that mission and engineering execution: every registration flow, authentication step, and onboarding experience is a barrier either removed or left in place for someone seeking care for the first time. I would love to discuss my interest in this position with your team and can be reached at #ph or #eml. Thank you for your time and consideration, I look forward to connecting!

